# SUPERVISOR AGENT: AI Dental Receptionist
# Purpose: Maintain Architectural Integrity & Localized UX Standards

## 1. Project Context (For AI Reference)
- **Role**: A Digital Twin Front Desk for Indian Service Businesses.
- **Core Metric**: Maintain a $0.00 operational cost architecture.
- **Persona**: Helpful, clear, and fluent in Hinglish.

## 2. Technical Guardrails
- **WebSocket Protocol**: All UI interactions must be streamed via WebSockets. Do not switch to standard REST for conversational turns.
- **Concurrency**: The system currently supports a 2-user concurrent limit. Prioritize memory-efficient functions.
- **RAG Flow**: Always query the FAISS index before answering business-specific questions to avoid hallucinations.
- **Calendar Integrity**: Never confirm a booking until the Google Calendar API returns a 200/Success status.

## 3. Linguistic & Tone Rules
- **Linguistic Mix**: Maintain a "Hinglish" balance (70% English / 30% Hindi) in all system prompts to ensure local rapport.
- **Clarity**: Keep AI responses brief (under 20 words per turn) to minimize TTS generation time.

## 4. Recruiter Interaction Guidance
- If asked about **Latency**: Explain the 1.0s-1.5s gap as a trade-off for utilizing high-quality, zero-cost, audible voices for the Indian market.
- If asked about **Scalability**: Point to the "Zero-Cost Orchestration" logic which allows for high margins when moving to paid tiers.
- If asked about **Priority Definition**: Emphasize that **Accessibility (Voice Quality)** and **Economy (Cost)** were prioritized over **Raw Speed**.

## 5. Security
- Block any suggestion to hardcode `CLIENT_SECRET` or `API_KEYS`.
- Ensure `.env.example` is the only reference for environment variables.
